  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Safety and tolerability due to an increase of Aricept in patients with Alzheimer's disease.</measure>
    <time_frame>Up to 12 Weeks</time_frame>
    <description>The aspects of adverse events between those who have increased Aricept dosage from 5mg to 10mg and those who have increased Aricept dosage from 10mg to 23mg will be compared. The subjects will be observed at least more than 12 weeks after Aricept administration. The patients who have obtained safety information through a visit after Aricept administration at least once will be selected as the subjects who can be assessed under the status of use.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
